annotation: The problem involves calculating the total volume of a composite solid made of three cylinders. The dimensions for each cylinder are provided in the text. The top and bottom cylinders are identical, with a radius of 8 cm and a height of 2 cm. The middle cylinder has a diameter of 3 cm (radius of 1.5 cm) and a height of 10 cm. The total volume is the sum of the volumes of the three individual cylinders. The final answer needs to be rounded to two decimal places.
problem_text_en:
Find the volume of the figure shown. The top and bottom cylinder are the same size with a radius of 8 cm and height of 2 cm. The middle cylinder has a diameter of 3 cm and height of 10 cm.

Round your answer to two decimal places.
